The paper discusses the use of cellular networks to provide connectivity for UAVs, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also analyzes the implications of changes in the radio environment with altitude, which involves robotics and control (cs.RO) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses potential enhancements for improving mobility performance, which involves cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
